import SigmaR.StandingAlgebra_FormalCore

/-!
###############################################################################
# Transformability Valuation Contract
###############################################################################

This file defines the governing interpretive rules of the
Transformability Valuation sub-layer in SigmaR.

Transformability valuation:
• evaluates effective ability to transform state under
  structural, contextual, and agreement-mediated conditions
• does not redefine operations or structural capability
• supports both internal and external transformability agreement
• incorporates aggregation, composability, and decomposability,
  from which abstraction structurally emerges
• encodes transformability-progress as a boundary condition,
  not a preference or selection rule
• treats omission of available transformability-progress as a
  structural constraint, not moral fault
• does not imply creativity, competence, merit, legitimacy,
  or authority
• does not authorize intervention or coercive action
• respects Independence, Monotonicity, Admissibility,
  and ResponseSemantics
• is always explicitly scoped

This file introduces no axioms.
###############################################################################
-/

namespace SigmaR

/--
The Transformability Valuation layer is governed by an explicit
interpretive contract defining its scope and limits.
-/
constant TransformabilityValuationContract : Prop

end SigmaR
